  "prompt": "What is the stage 2 hypertension diet?",
  "response": "A stage 2 hypertension diet typically focuses on reducing blood pressure through dietary changes. Here are key recommendations:\n\n1. DASH Diet Principles\n- Low sodium intake (less than 1,500 mg/day)\n- High in fruits and vegetables\n- Whole grains\n- Lean proteins\n- Low-fat dairy products\n\n2. Specific Dietary Guidelines\n- Reduce processed foods\n- Limit saturated and trans fats\n- Minimize added sugars\n- Increase potassium-rich foods\n- Moderate alcohol consumption\n\n3. Recommended Foods\n- Leafy green vegetables\n- Berries\n- Bananas\n- Sweet potatoes\n- Fatty fish (salmon, mackerel)\n- Nuts and seeds\n- Legumes\n- Olive oil\n\n4. Foods to Avoid\n- High-sodium processed foods\n- Red meat\n- Fried foods\n- Sugary beverages\n- Excessive caffeine\n- Alcohol\n\n5. Additional Recommendations\n- Control portion sizes\n- Stay hydrated\n- Consider reducing overall calorie intake if overweight\n- Regular exercise\n\nAlways consult a healthcare professional or registered dietitian for personalized dietary advice specific to your health condition.",
